  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "22:20-24 This chapter ends with some account of Nahor's family, who had settled at Haran. This seems to be given for the connexion which it had with the church of God. From thence Isaac and Jacob took wives; and before the account of those events this list is recorded. It shows that though Abraham saw his own family highly honoured with privileges, admitted into covenant, and blessed with the assurance of the promise, yet he did not look with disdain upon his relations, but was glad to hear of the increase and welfare of their families.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This family notice is inserted as a piece of contemporaneous history, to explain and prepare the way for the marriage of Isaac. \"Milkah, she also,\" in allusion to Sarah, who has borne Isaac. So far as we know, they may have been sisters, but they were at all events sisters-in-law. The only new persons belonging to our histoy are Bethuel and Rebekah. Uz, Aram, and Kesed are interesting, as they show that we are in the region of the Shemites, among whom these are ancestral names ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 10:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 11:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Buz may have been the ancestor of Elihu ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 25:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 32:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Maakah may have given rise to the tribes and land of Maakah ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 3:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 10:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The other names do not again occur. \"And his concubine.\" A concubine was a secondary wife, whose position was not considered disreputable in the East. Nahor, like Ishmael, had twelve sons, - eight by his wife, and four by his concubine. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - The Death of Sarah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2. ארבע קרית  qı̂ryat-'arba‛, \"Qirjath-arba', city of Arba.\" ארבע  'arba‛, \"Arba', four.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "8. עפרון  ‛eprôn, \"'Ephron, of the dust, or resembling a calf.\" צחר  tshochar, \"Tsochar, whiteness.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "9. מכפלה  makpêlâh, \"Makpelah, doubled.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The death and burial of Sarah are here recorded. This occasions the purchase of the field of Makpelah, in the cave of which is her sepulchre.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "The death and burial of Sarah are here recorded. This occasions the purchase of the field of Makpelah, in the cave of which is her sepulchre.",
            "children": []
          },
